    "fields": {
      "summary": "Node Manager to use openFile() with whole-file read policy for localizing files.",
      "issuetype": {
        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issuetype/4",
        "id": "4",
        "description": "An improvement or enhancement to an existing feature or task.",
        "iconUrl": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=21140&avatarType=issuetype",
        "name": "Improvement",
        "subtask": false,
        "avatarId": 21140
      },
      "components": [
        {
          "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/component/12319323",
          "id": "12319323",
          "name": "nodemanager"
        }
      ],
      "subtasks": [],
      "created": "2020-09-18T18:34:19.788+0000",
      "description": "\r\nHADOOP-16202 adds standard options for declaring the read/seek\r\nPolicy when reading a file. These should be set to sequential IO\r\nWhen localising resources, so that if the default/cluster settings\r\nFor a file system are optimized for random IO, artifact downloads\r\nare still read at the maximum speed possible (one big GET to the EOF).\r\n\r\nMost of this happens in hadoop-common, but some tuning of FSDownload\r\ncan assist\r\n\r\n* tar/jar download must also be sequential\r\n* if the FileStatus is passed around, that can be used\r\n  in the open request to skip checks when loading the file.\r\n  \r\nTogether this can save 3 HEAD requests per resource, with the sequential\r\nIO avoiding any splitting of the big read into separate block GETs",
      "priority": {
        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/priority/4",
        "iconUrl": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/priorities/minor.svg",
